	📊 Power BI Dashboard Structure
Page 1 — Market Overview
Price trends
Market comparisons
Key KPIs

Objective: Understand macro energy market evolution.

Page 2 — Risk Analytics
Daily returns
Rolling volatility
Value at Risk (VaR)

Objective: Measure market risk and turbulence.

Page 3 — Correlation Analysis
Rolling correlations
Scatter plots
Cross-market dependencies

Key Insight:

Gas markets drive electricity price behavior in Europe.

Page 4 — Performance Analytics
Sharpe ratios (rolling)
Drawdowns
Maximum drawdown comparison

Objective: Evaluate risk-adjusted performance.

Page 5 — Trading Strategy Insights
Crisis period analysis
Market contagion effects
Portfolio implications
🔑 Key Findings
TTF Natural Gas exhibited the highest volatility across all markets.
Electricity prices strongly follow gas price dynamics.
Correlations increase significantly during crisis periods (2022).
Carbon markets act as volatility amplifiers.
Oil markets remain comparatively stable.
